adjectives.description: rustproof (comparative more rustproof, superlative most rustproof)

entries.meaning: Resistant to rust, oxidation and corrosion.
examples: This is supposed to be a rustproof trashcan, but it can't handle the salt they use on our roads.

verbs.description: rustproof (third-person singular simple present rustproofs, present participle rustproofing, simple past and past participle rustproofed)

entries.meaning: To make resistant to rust, such as by applying a coating.
examples: We'll rustproof the metal with a good coat of paint and then we'll be able to leave it outdoors for years without damage.
